@@TJvCheckListBox.DeleteExactString@string@Boolean@Boolean
Description:
Call this method to delete a string of the list. This method can either delete all or only the first occurence of the string.

Parameters:
Value - is the string you want to search for.
All - is true if you want to delete all occurences of the string
CaseSensitive - is true if the search is case sensitive, false if not.



Returns:
X: the index of the item in the list.

-1: if the string hasn't been found.

================================================================
@@TJvCheckListBox.DeleteSelected
Description:
Call this method to delete all selected elements of the list. If the MultiSelect property is false, it only deletes the element indiced by the itemindex property. But if the MultiSelect property is true, it deletes all selected items.

